<br>
You know, I was thinking about the gatling gun, and I think it appear that way because of the nozel. On the original, which is slightly bigger, you can see the tubes going inward, and it makes sense.<br>
<br>
Well, the tutorial will actually sway away from the typical &quot;step-by-step&quot; format you see. It is mostly about the thought process behind designing vehicles overall, how to think about schematics and where one can be creative and where they need to use some simple logic. More of a short lecture than a tutorial, really.<br>
<br>
But I see that a lot of you have been asking for a tutorial of how to draw 3/4 views of vehicles lately. Maybe that will come next <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The best advice I can give at the moment is to just move the vanishing point about 3 or 4 feet off the paper and 2 or 3 feet up. Imaginary, of course. <p><a href="http://www.svmaerospace.cjb.net"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/wufei736/images/svmsig.txt 
